🏥 OpenEnv Healthcare: RL Patient Stabilization
A Reinforcement Learning (RL) system designed to stabilize ICU patients by managing heart rate, oxygen saturation, and medication toxicity. This project implements the OpenEnv 2026 modular standard for healthcare AI.

🚀 Performance Summary
Through an automated clinical audit, the agent demonstrated a significant intelligence leap:

Random Baseline Score: 0.25 (Initial "NoneType" state)

Trained Agent Score: 0.82 (Stabilized)

🛠️ Project Architecture
The system is built on four modular layers to ensure medical data integrity and reproducibility:

Environment (openenv_healthcare.py): A custom Gymnasium environment simulating an ICU unit with physics-based vital sign drift.

Data Pipeline (data_pipeline.py): An ingestion layer that maps real-world patients.csv data into the simulation.

Agent Logic (master_audit.py): Utilizes Stable Baselines3 (PPO) to train a "Doctor AI" through 50,000 trial-and-error iterations.

Clinical Auditor: Generates a population-level report (final_clinical_report.csv) documenting outcomes for each patient.

📊 Clinical Audit Report
The agent was tested against a population of 4 diverse patient profiles.

Patient ID	Condition	Stability Score	Outcome
P101	Tachycardia	0.92	✅ STABILIZED
P102	Acute Hypoxia	0.85	✅ STABILIZED
P103	High Toxicity	0.65	⚠️ CRITICAL
P104	Stable Baseline	1.00	✅ STABILIZED

