📊 Clinical Audit Report
The agent was tested against a population of 4 diverse patient profiles.

Patient ID	Condition	Stability Score	Outcome
P101	Tachycardia	0.92	✅ STABILIZED
P102	Acute Hypoxia	0.85	✅ STABILIZED
P103	High Toxicity	0.65	⚠️ CRITICAL
P104	Stable Baseline	1.00	✅ STABILIZED
Note: Patient P103 represents a "Safe Failure" where the agent chose to withhold medication to prevent lethal toxicity, prioritizing long-term safety over short-term vitals.

💻 Technical Setup
Prerequisites
Python 3.10+

gymnasium

stable-baselines3

pandas

matplotlib

Installation & Execution
Run the Master Audit:
This script handles the training, evaluation, and report generation in one go.

Bash
python master_audit.py
Generate Visualization:

Bash
python generate_chart.py
🧠 Core AI Concepts Used
Observation Space: 3-dimensional Box (Heart Rate, O 
2
​
  Saturation, Toxicity).

Action Space: Discrete (0: Wait, 1: Beta-Blocker, 2: Oxygen).

Reward Function: Dense binary reward (+1.0/-1.0) to penalize instability and toxicity.

Optimization: Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) with a custom learning rate.

📈 Future Roadmap
Multi-Agent Systems: Coordinating between a "Doctor Agent" and a "Nurse Agent."

Continuous Action Spaces: Moving from discrete doses to continuous medication titration.

FHIR Integration: Direct API connection to live hospital record systems.
